org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.records

Class AllocationTagNamespace

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.records.AllocationTagNamespace
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Evaluable<TargetApplications>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllocationTagNamespace.All, AllocationTagNamespace.AppID, AllocationTagNamespace.AppLabel, AllocationTagNamespace.NotSelf, AllocationTagNamespace.Self

    public abstract class AllocationTagNamespace
extends Object
implements Evaluable<TargetApplications>
    Class to describe the namespace of an allocation tag. Each namespace can be evaluated against a set of applications. After evaluation, the namespace should have an implicit set of applications which defines its scope.

      • isGlobal

        public boolean isGlobal()
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is effective in all applications in this cluster. Specifically the namespace prefix should be "all".

      • isSingleInterApp

        public boolean isSingleInterApp()
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is effective within a single application by its application ID, the namespace prefix should be "app-id"; false otherwise.

      • isIntraApp

        public boolean isIntraApp()
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is effective to the application itself, the namespace prefix should be "self"; false otherwise.

      • isNotSelf

        public boolean isNotSelf()
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is effective to all applications except itself, the namespace prefix should be "not-self"; false otherwise.

      • isAppLabel

        public boolean isAppLabel()
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is effective to a group of applications identified by a application label, the namespace prefix should be "app-label"; false otherwise.
